summary: High-energy but irritable day. Maintained routine and studied well. Got a call from Google recruiter, asked for 3 weeks to prepare. Experienced irritation and anger during a conversation with dad, cut the call twice after he interrupted while discussing Tanvi and asked about meds, which felt like weaponizing bipolar. Feeling conflicted about whether the reaction was justified.

wins: Proactively asked Google recruiter for time to prepare
losses: Cut the call twice which might feel impulsive
ideas: Explore ways to assert boundaries calmly when mental health is weaponized
Use anger as signal to protect personal conversations

goals: Practice emotional regulation in triggering conversations
triggerEvents: Questioned about meds in a way that felt weaponizing
